<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <title>HTML Lists</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial;
            background: #f4f6f9;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .container {
            width: 90%;
            margin: auto;
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px #ccc;
        }

        h1 {
            background: #2980b9;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px;
        }

        .row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 10px;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        .box {
            flex: 1;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding: 10px;
        }

        .code {
            background: #eef2f7;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            background: #2980b9;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .center {
            text-align: left;
            margin-top: 15px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>HTML Lists: Ordered and Unordered</h1>
        <p>Understand the difference between ordered and unordered lists.</p>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="box">
                <h3>Ordered List</h3>
                Items in sequence:
                <div class="code">
                    &lt;ol&gt;<br>
                    &lt;li&gt;First&lt;/li&gt;<br>
                    &lt;li&gt;Second&lt;/li&gt;<br>
                    &lt;li&gt;Third&lt;/li&gt;<br>
                    &lt;/ol&gt;
                </div>
                <br>Preview:
                <ol>
                    <li>First</li>
                    <li>Second</li>
                    <li>Third</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <div class="box">
                <h3>Unordered List</h3>
                Bullet points:
                <div class="code">
                    &lt;ul&gt;<br>
                    &lt;li&gt;Apple&lt;/li&gt;<br>
                    &lt;li&gt;Banana&lt;/li&gt;<br>
                    &lt;li&gt;Cherry&lt;/li&gt;<br>
                    &lt;/ul&gt;
                </div>
                <br>Preview:
                <ul>
                    <li>Apple</li>
                    <li>Banana</li>
                    <li>Cherry</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <h3>Summary</h3>
        <p>Ordered lists use numbers. Unordered lists use bullets.</p>
        <div class="center">
            <a href="Page1.html" class="btn">← Back</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>
